OL,3,CCoroner urges action on road deaths
OL,4,Ccaused by drivers with failing eyesight
OL,6,FThe Department for Transport said it
OL,7,Fwould consider the coroner's report
OL,8,Fonce received.
OL,10,FA spokesperson added: "The NHS
OL,11,Frecommends adults should have their
OL,12,Feyes tested every two years and
OL,13,Fdrivers are legally required to inform
OL,14,Fthe DVLA if they have a condition
OL,15,Fwhich affects their eyesight.
OL,17,F"We are committed to improving road
OL,18,Fsafety and continue to explore ways to
OL,19,Fachieve this."
